<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-607-188  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 607 188.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Government Computer News  Sept 4 1989 v8 n18 p74(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Ziff-Davis Pub. Co. 1989.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Air situation display system ties bases together. (project tocombine Air Force outposts)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Green, Robert.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Topic:     MilitaryComputer Systems IntegrationDecision Support SystemsCommand and Control SystemsUnited States. Air Force.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>Air Situation Display System Ties Bases TogetherandM;An effort to combine two Air Force outposts in West Germany into a singleSector Air Operations Center (SOC) was boosted in June with the delivery of anew Air Situation Display System (ASDS) to the U.S.-NATO tactical operationscenter at Sembach Air Base, near the East German border.andM;Provided under a $3.6 million contract by integrator Comptek Research Inc. ofBuffalo, N.Y., the system consists of color monitors, desktop terminals,interfaces to the center's resident Digital Equipment Corp.andP;  MicroVAX system,an off-the-shelf graphics package and 30,000 lines of Ada code.andM;Lt.andP;  Lisa Meyers, ASDS program manager, said a commander who formerly ranboth Sembach and Boerfink Air Base, working at either one of the two basessituated 55 miles apart, now has both offensive and defensive data availableto him at Sembach.andM;As well, Meyers said, decisions formerly based on telephone conversations andgrease-pencil overlays will be facilitated by the Comptek system.andM;&quot;The real benefit is that the commander can see the picture himself,&quot; shesaid.andP;  &quot;He's not talking over the phone to someone else who's trying todescribe it.&quot;andM;Information collected principally by radar systems goes to a 5118 mainframefrom Hughes Aircraft Corp. at the nearby Control Reporting Center.andP;  &quot;The rawradar data has to be processed by the Hughes machine before it can bedisplayed, so we have a near real-time, rather than a real-time system,&quot; shesaid.andM;After the Hughes machine processes the information, it is ported to the SOC.andO;The MicroVAX running the Ada software distributes the air picture to sixdifferent off-the-shelf DECsystem 3100 workstations.andM;SOC terminal operators can manipulate pictures on their 19-inch monitors, andzoom in or isolate areas, though the ASDS is basically a receive-only system,Meyers said.andM;ASDS was a joint development and procurement effort of the Air Force'sElectronic Systems Division at Hanscom Air Force Base, Mass., and theservice's European command in West Germany.andP;  The system is expected to befully operational by the end of the year, an ESD spokeswoman said.andO;</TEXT></DOC>